                        "content": "A client presents at the primary health care provider's office with complaints of a bull's-eye rash on his upper leg. Which question would the nurse ask first?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe nurse would ask questions to assist in identifying the cause of Lyme disease, which is a multisystem infection that results from a bite by a tick carried by several species of deer. The rash from a tick bite can be a ringlike rash occurring 3 to 4 weeks after a bite and is commonly seen on the groin, buttocks, axillae, trunk, or upper arms or legs. Option 1 is referring to toxoplasmosis, which is caused by the inhalation of cysts from contaminated cat feces. Lyme disease cannot be transmitted from one person to another.",
                        "id": "00258e52103a48dbada494ae3dd771b7",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e10f5f4e112b9b63e47a8c3aa1fab0ca",
                                "content": "Ultraviolet light therapy"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "649d0896b9c18f7d3cf0ce1e69edd8c3",
                                "content": "A 14- to 21-day course of doxycycline"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3f2453c235bdd9fb23cdee17713f08f7",
                                "content": "No treatment unless symptoms develop"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d7cfb3792e7984c0685d73fcb6708d00",
                                "content": "Treatment with intravenous (IV) penicillin G"
