                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "<p>A client suspected of having stage I Lyme disease is seen in the health care clinic and is told that the Lyme disease test result is positive. The client asks the nurse about the treatment for the disease. In responding to the client, the nurse anticipates that which intervention will be part of the treatment plan?</p>",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationale:</p><p>Lyme disease is a reportable systemic infectious disease caused by the spirochete Borellia burgdorferi and results from the bite of an infected deer tick, also known as the black-legged tick. A 14 to 21-day course of oral antibiotic therapy is recommended during stage I. Later stages of Lyme disease may require therapy with IV antibiotics, such as penicillin G. Ultraviolet light therapy is not a component of the treatment plan for Lyme disease.</p><p>Test-Taking Strategy:</p><p>Focus on the subject,&nbsp;treatment for Lyme disease. Note that the question specifies stage I. Eliminate option 4 because IV antibiotics will not be administered in this stage. Eliminate option 1 because this is not a component of the treatment for Lyme disease. Waiting for symptoms to develop is incorrect, so eliminate option 3.</p>",
                        "id": "12e6c2da490b46be8af8038911b80ccb",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9fc3d05512744566923eb8d3c78c1bfb",
                                "content": "Skin rash"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5e6571e4aa124a98bbe38d15106bea60",
                                "content": "Arthralgias"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "91d40253271742e0bc0f72bbf50c3de8",
                                "content": "Neurological deficits"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4037104ce4864248bb669adac162f284",
                                "content": "Enlarged and inflamed joints"
                            }
                        ],
