                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nLyme disease is a reportable systemic infectious disease caused by the spirochete Borellia burgdorferi and results from the bite of an infected deer tick, also known as the black-legged tick. Prevention, public education, and early diagnosis are vital to the control and treatment of Lyme disease. A 14- to 21-day course of oral antibiotic therapy is recommended during stage I. Later stages of Lyme disease may require therapy with intravenously administered antibiotics, such as penicillin G. The remaining options are incorrect.",
